{"questionId":"31911275","questionHtml":"<p>Two Manx cats are selected at random from a large population. Find the probability that they both have a mass less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi>kg</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>multiplying two identical probabilities <em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>W</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>×</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>W</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp;</strong></em><strong> OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>their</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>×</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>their</mi><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo></math></strong><em><strong><br></strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Accept a lower bound of zero for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi></math>, given the context.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>00620967</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0000386</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0000385601</mn><mo>…</mo></math> &nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>)</mo></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M0A0</strong></em> for an answer greater than&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> such as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn></math>.<br>Award <em><strong>M1A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>86</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">E</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"31911275","referenceCode":"24N.1.AHL.TZ0.3c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Two Manx cats are selected at random from a large population. Find the probability that they both have a mass less than 3.5 kg.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}